      "variant": "main",
      "html": "\n\n\n<h4><span>Solve Applications of Systems of Inequalities</span></h4>\n<p><span>When we use variables other than \\(x\\)&nbsp;and \\(y\\)&nbsp;to define an unknown quantity, we must change the names of the axes of the graph as well.</span></p>\n<p><span>Example:</span>&nbsp;Omar needs to eat at least 800 calories before going to his team practice. All he wants is hamburgers, \\(h\\), and cookies, \\(c\\), and he doesn&rsquo;t want to spend more than $5. At the hamburger restaurant near his college, each hamburger has 240 calories and costs $1.40. Each cookie has 160 calories and costs $0.50.</p>\n\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li>Write a system of inequalities to model this situation.</li>\n<li>Graph the system.</li>\n<li>Could he eat 3 hamburgers and 1 cookie?</li>\n<li>Could he eat 2 hamburgers and 4 cookies?</li>\n</ol>\n\n<div data-type=\"example\" id=\"fs-id1167836662838\">\n<section>\n<div>\n<div data-type=\"exercise\" id=\"fs-id1167836507645\">\n<section>\n<div data-type=\"problem\" id=\"fs-id1167836628288\">\n<div>\n\n<h4>Solution</h4>\n<p id=\"fs-idm353582128\">a.)<br></p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"left\">Let<span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;the number of hamburgers&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;mo&gt;.&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;the number of hamburgers&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;mo&gt;.&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-78-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\">&nbsp;\\(h=\\)<nobr aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1215\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1216\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1217\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1218\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1219\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1222\">the number of hamburgers and \\(c=\\) the number of cookies.</span></span></span></span></span></span></nobr></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"left\">To find the system of equations, translate the information.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"left\">The calories from hamburgers at 240 calories each, plus the calories from cookies at 160 calories each</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"left\">must be at least 800.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"center\"><span>\\(240h+160c\\geq800\\)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mspace width=\"3em\" /&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;The amount spent on hamburgers at $1.40 each, plus the amount spent on cookies at $0.50 each&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mspace width=\"3em\"&gt;&lt;/mspace&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;The amount spent on hamburgers at $1.40 each, plus the amount spent on cookies at $0.50 each&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-81-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\">\n<nobr aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1245\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1246\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1247\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1248\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1249\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1251\">The amount spent on hamburgers at $1.40 each, plus the amount spent on cookies at $0.50 each</span></span></span></span></span></span></nobr>\n</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mspace width=\"3em\" /&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;must be no more than $5.00.&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mspace width=\"3em\"&gt;&lt;/mspace&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;must be no more than $5.00.&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-82-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\">\n<nobr aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1252\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1253\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1254\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1255\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1256\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1258\">must be no more than $5.00.</span></span></span></span></span></span></nobr><span role=\"presentation\"><math display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"></math>&nbsp;</span>\n</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"center\"><span>\\(1.40h+0.50c\\leq5\\)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mspace width=\"3em\" /&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;The number of hamburgers must be greater than or equal to 0.&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mspace width=\"3em\"&gt;&lt;/mspace&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;The number of hamburgers must be greater than or equal to 0.&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-84-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\">\n<nobr aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1271\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1272\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1273\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1274\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1275\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1277\">The number of hamburgers must be greater than or equal to 0.</span></span></span></span></span></span></nobr>\n</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"center\"><span>\\(h\\geq0\\)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mspace width=\"3em\" /&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;The number of cookies must be greater than or equal to 0.&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mspace width=\"3em\"&gt;&lt;/mspace&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;The number of cookies must be greater than or equal to 0.&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-86-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\"><span role=\"presentation\">\n<semantics>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mtext>The number of cookies must be greater than or equal to 0.</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</span>\n</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"center\"><span>\\(c\\geq0\\)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td data-align=\"left\">We have our system of equations.&nbsp;<span>\\(\\left\\{\\begin{array}{l}240h\\;+\\;160c\\;\\geq\\;800\\\\1.40h\\;+0.50c\\;\\leq\\;5\\\\h\\;\\geq\\;0\\\\c\\;\\geq\\;0\\end{array}\\right.\\)</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167833310128\"><br></p>\n<p><span data-type=\"newline\">b.)<br></span>Since \\(h\\geq0\\)<span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-89-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\"><span role=\"presentation\">\n<semantics>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>&nbsp;</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</span></span>and \\(c\\geq0\\)<span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-90-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\">\n<nobr aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1347\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1348\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1349\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1350\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-1351\"></span></span></span></span></span></nobr>\n</span><span>(both are greater than or equal to zero), all solutions will be in the first quadrant. As a result, our graph shows only quadrant one.</span></p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"fs-id1167833136536\">\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\">To graph \\(240h+160c\\geq80\\)<span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;240&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;160&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2265;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;800&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;240&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;160&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&ge;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;800&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-91-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\"><span role=\"presentation\">\n<semantics>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mo>,</mo>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</span></span>graph<span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;240&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;160&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;800&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;240&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;160&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;800&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-92-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\">&nbsp;\\(240h+160c=800\\)&nbsp;</span>as a solid line.<span data-type=\"newline\"><br></span>Choose \\((0, 0)\\) as a test point. Since it does not make the inequality true, shade (red) the side that does not include the point \\((0, 0)\\).</td>\n<td data-align=\"left\" data-valign=\"top\"><span data-alt=\".\" data-type=\"media\" id=\"fs-id1167833136523\"><img alt=\"graph of 240h+160c is greater than or equal to 800 and graph of 1.40h +0.50c is less than or equal to 5\" class=\"img-fluid atto_image_button_text-bottom\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/a33241cd08b3ea9848101b3823e7dcf56f94a8ac\" width=\"300\"></span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p id=\" fs-id1167833239251\">Graph \\(1.40h+0.50c\\leq5\\)<span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1.40&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0.50&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2264;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;5&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;.&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1.40&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0.50&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&le;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;5&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;.&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-93-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\"><span role=\"presentation\">\n<semantics>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mo>.</mo>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</span></span>The boundary line is \\(1.40h+0.50c=5\\)<span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"inline\"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1.40&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0.50&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;5&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;.&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\"&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1.40&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0.50&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;5&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;.&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/annotation-xml&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-94-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\"><span role=\"presentation\">\n<semantics>\n<annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\">\n<mrow>\n<mo>.</mo>\n</mrow>\n</annotation-xml>\n</semantics>\n</span></span>We test \\((0, 0)\\), and it makes the inequality true. We shade the side of the line that includes \\((0, 0)\\).</p>\n\n<p id=\"fs-id1167836512397\">The solution of the system is the region of the graph that is shaded the darkest. The boundary line sections that border the darkly shaded section are included in the solution, as are the points on the&nbsp;\\(x\\)-axis from \\((5, 0)\\) to \\((10, 0)\\).</p>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167833135690\">c.) To determine if 3 hamburgers and 1 cookie would meet Omar&rsquo;s criteria, we see if the point \\((3, 2)\\) is in the solution region. It is, so Omar might choose to eat 3 hamburgers and 1 cookie.</p>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167829942426\">d.) To determine if 2 hamburgers and 4 cookies would meet Omar&rsquo;s criteria, we see if the point \\((2, 4)\\) is in the solution region. It is, so Omar might choose to eat 2 hamburgers and 4 cookies.</p>\n<p id=\"fs-id1167836559981\">We could also test the possible solutions by substituting the values into each inequality.</p>\n</div>\n<h4><br></h4>\n<h4>Try It: Solve Applications of Systems of Inequalities</h4>\n</section>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"Reveal1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n\n<ol>\n<li>Philip&rsquo;s doctor tells him he should add at least 1,000 more calories per day to his usual diet. Philip wants to buy protein bars, \\(p\\), that cost $1.80 each and have 140 calories and juice, \\(j\\), that costs $1.25 per bottle and has 125 calories. He doesn&rsquo;t want to spend more than $12.<ol type=\"a\">\n<li>Write a system of inequalities that models this situation.</li>\n<li>Graph the system.</li>\n<li>Can he buy 3 protein bars and 5 bottles of juice?</li>\n<li>Can he buy 5 protein bars and 3 bottles of juice?</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n<p>Write down your answer. Then select the <strong>Solution</strong> button to check your work.\n    </p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"Reveal1\">\n\n<p><span>Here is how to write and graph this system of inequalities to find solutions:</span><br></p>\n\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li>\\(\\left\\{\\begin{array}{l}140p+125j\\geq1000\\\\1.80p+1.25j\\leq12\\end{array}\\right.\\)<br><strong><img alt=\"This figure shows a graph on an x y-coordinate plane of 140p + 125j is greater than or equal to 1000 and 1.80p + 1.25j is less than or equal to 12. The area to the left or right of each line is shaded slightly different colors with the overlapping area also shaded a slightly different color.\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/cd86af0c8064a34c9427585198c49de9e2e7945f\"></strong><br></li>\n<li><strong></strong></li>\n<li>yes</li>\n<li>no</li>\n</ol>\n<p><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-9f4b4fde-7fff-e24d-2267-49648e0eb6dd\"></b></p>\n<div align=\"left\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p>How did you do? Know that you learn more from wrong answers than from right answers! Wrong answers help us find flaws in our thinking. Take a minute to think about why you got the question wrong. Then you won&rsquo;t get this type of question wrong again!</p>\n</div>\n\n</div>"
    }
